<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3686] fix solr/core and solr/solrj not to share a lib/ directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3686</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This makes the build system hairy.&lt;br/&gt;
it also prevents us from using ivy&apos;s sync=true (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-4262&quot; title=&quot;add ivy sync=true, consolidate licensing, disallow conflicting dependencies&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUCENE-4262&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-4262&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;br/&gt;
which totally prevents the issue of outdated jars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should fix this so each has its own lib/&lt;/p&gt;</description>
